profile_properties.name: altLabel
label: alternative label
definition: An alternative lexical label for a resource.
comment: Acronyms, abbreviations, spelling variants, and irregular plural/singular forms may be included among the alternative labels for a concept. Mis-spelled terms are normally included as hidden labels (see skos:hiddenLabel).
ontology_entities.name: altLabel

profile_properties.name: broader
label: has broader
definition: A concept that is more general in meaning.
comment: Broader concepts are typically rendered as parents in a concept hierarchy (tree).
ontology_entities.name: broader

profile_properties.name: changeNote
label: change note
definition: A note about a modification to a concept.
ontology_entities.name: changeNote

profile_properties.name: definition
label: definition
definition: A statement or formal explanation of the meaning of a concept.
ontology_entities.name: definition

profile_properties.name: editorialNote
label: editorial note
definition: A note for an editor, translator or maintainer of the vocabulary.
ontology_entities.name: editorialNote

profile_properties.name: example
label: example
definition: An example of the use of a concept.
ontology_entities.name: example

profile_properties.name: hiddenLabel
label: hidden label
definition: A lexical label for a resource that should be hidden when generating visual displays of the resource, but should still be accessible to free text search operations.
ontology_entities.name: hiddenLabel

profile_properties.name: historyNote
label: history note
comment: A note about the past state/use/meaning of a concept.
ontology_entities.name: historyNote

profile_properties.name: inScheme
label: in scheme
definition: A concept scheme in which the concept is included.
comment: A concept may be a member of more than one concept scheme.
ontology_entities.name: inScheme

profile_properties.name: narrower
label: has narrower
definition: A concept that is more specific in meaning.
comment: Narrower concepts are typically rendered as children in a concept hierarchy (tree).
ontology_entities.name: narrower

profile_properties.name: note
label: note
definition: A general note, for any purpose.
comment: This property may be used directly, or as a super-property for more specific note types.
ontology_entities.name: note

profile_properties.name: prefLabel
label: preferred label
definition: The preferred lexical label for a resource, in a given language.
comment: No two concepts in the same concept scheme may have the same value for skos:prefLabel in a given language.
ontology_entities.name: prefLabel

profile_properties.name: related
label: related to
definition: A concept with which there is an associative semantic relationship.
ontology_entities.name: related

profile_properties.name: scopeNote
label: scope note
definition: A note that helps to clarify the meaning of a concept.
ontology_entities.name: scopeNote

profile_properties.name: label
label: label
definition: A human-readable name for the subject.
ontology_entities.name: label

profile_properties.name: hasTopConcept
label: has top concept
definition: Relates, by convention, a concept scheme to a concept which is topmost in the broader/narrower concept hierarchies for that scheme, providing an entry point to these hierarchies.
ontology_entities.name: hasTopConcept

profile_properties.name: topConceptOf
label: top concept of
definition: Relates a concept to the concept scheme that it is a top level concept of.
ontology_entities.name: topConceptOf

profile_properties.name: ConceptScheme
label: Concept Scheme
definition: A set of concepts, optionally including statements about semantic relationships between those concepts.
comment: A concept scheme may be defined to include concepts from different sources.
ontology_entities.name: ConceptScheme

profile_properties.name: broadMatch
label: has broader match
definition: skos:broadMatch is used to state a hierarchical mapping link between two conceptual resources in different concept schemes.
ontology_entities.name: broadMatch

profile_properties.name: narrowMatch
label: has narrower match
definition: skos:narrowMatch is used to state a hierarchical mapping link between two conceptual resources in different concept schemes.
ontology_entities.name: narrowMatch

profile_properties.name: relatedMatch
label: has related match
definition: skos:relatedMatch is used to state an associative mapping link between two conceptual resources in different concept schemes.
ontology_entities.name: relatedMatch

profile_properties.name: exactMatch
label: has exact match
definition: skos:exactMatch is used to link two concepts, indicating a high degree of confidence that the concepts can be used interchangeably across a wide range of information retrieval applications. skos:exactMatch is a transitive property, and is a sub-property of skos:closeMatch.
comment: skos:exactMatch is disjoint with each of the properties skos:broadMatch and skos:relatedMatch.
ontology_entities.name: exactMatch

profile_properties.name: closeMatch
label: has close match
definition: skos:closeMatch is used to link two concepts that are sufficiently similar that they can be used interchangeably in some information retrieval applications. In order to avoid the possibility of "compound errors" when combining mappings across more than two concept schemes, skos:closeMatch is not declared to be a transitive property.
ontology_entities.name: closeMatch

profile_properties.name: mappingRelation
label: is in mapping relation with
definition: Relates two concepts coming, by convention, from different schemes, and that have comparable meanings
comment: These concept mapping relations mirror semantic relations, and the data model defined below is similar (with the exception of skos:exactMatch) to the data model defined for semantic relations. A distinct vocabulary is provided for concept mapping relations, to provide a convenient way to differentiate links within a concept scheme from links between concept schemes. However, this pattern of usage is not a formal requirement of the SKOS data model, and relies on informal definitions of best practice.
ontology_entities.name: mappingRelation

profile_properties.name: altSymbol
label: alternative symbolic label
definition: An alternative symbolic label for a resource.
ontology_entities.name: altSymbol

profile_properties.name: isSubjectOf
label: is subject of
definition: A resource for which the concept is a subject.
ontology_entities.name: isSubjectOf

profile_properties.name: isPrimarySubjectOf
label: is primary subject of
definition: A resource for which the concept is the primary subject.
ontology_entities.name: isPrimarySubjectOf

profile_properties.name: prefSymbol
label: preferred symbolic label
definition: The preferred symbolic label for a resource.
comment: No two concepts in the same concept scheme may have the same value for skos:prefSymbol.
ontology_entities.name: prefSymbol

profile_properties.name: primarySubject
label: has primary subject
definition: A concept that is the primary subject of the resource.
comment: A resource may have only one primary subject per concept scheme.
ontology_entities.name: primarySubject

profile_properties.name: subject
label: has subject
definition: A concept that is a subject of the resource.
comment: The following rule may be applied for this property: [(?d skos:subject ?x)(?x skos:broader ?y) implies (?d skos:subject ?y)]
ontology_entities.name: subject

profile_properties.name: subjectIndicator
label: subject indicator
definition: A subject indicator for a concept. [The notion of 'subject indicator' is defined here with reference to the latest definition endorsed by the OASIS Published Subjects Technical Committee.]
comment: This property allows subject indicators to be used for concept identification in place of or in addition to directly assigned URIs.
ontology_entities.name: subjectIndicator

profile_properties.name: symbol
label: symbolic label
definition: An image that is a symbolic label for the resource.
comment: This property is roughly analagous to rdfs:label, but for labelling resources with images that have retrievable representations, rather than RDF literals.
ontology_entities.name: symbol
